# Members

A member represents a person, family, shared accommodation, or company, and allows you to manage their information (address, contact details, etc.). A member's membership is managed via their subscriptions, with only one subscription per fiscal year.

A member is created through the [registration form](<%= new_members_member_url(subdomain: Current.org.members_subdomain) %>) or by an admin through the [member creation form](/members/new).

## Statuses {#statuses}

### To validate

New members created using the [registration form](<%= new_members_member_url(subdomain: Current.org.members_subdomain) %>) are added to [the list of members to validate](/members?scope=pending). They must be validated by an administrator to ensure that all information is correct.

It is possible to automatically send a welcome email when validating a member by configuring [the "Member validated" email template](/mail_templates/member_validated).

> Administrators can be notified by email when a new registration occurs by managing their [notification preferences](<%= edit_admin_path(current_admin) %>).

### Waiting list

Once validated, or directly created by an admin, a member with a (pending) subscription configuration ends up on the waiting list. The waiting list is useful for organizations that have a capacity limit on active members.

To make a member active, simply create a subscription for them (click "Create a subscription" at the top right of the member's page). The (pending) subscription configuration is automatically carried into the subscription creation form.

It is possible to automatically send a welcome email when activating a member by configuring [the "Member activated" email template](/mail_templates/member_activated).

### Active

An active member is one who has a subscription for the current or future fiscal year. A member who has a defined depot for grocery orders is also considered active.

As soon as the current subscription is ended or deleted, the member becomes inactive.

### Support

A support member is one without any subscriptions who has an annual fee set (for associations) or who owns [share capital](/handbook/billing#share-capital) (for cooperatives). If a subscription is created for a support member, they become active.

To move an inactive member to support, simply set an annual fee amount in the member's profile (edit page). The annual fee can be set to 0 for members who should have the support status without paying any fee.

Using the "Make inactive" button at the top right of the member's page, it is possible to make a support member inactive, which will remove their annual fee or set their required share capital to zero.

Using the "Put on waiting list" button at the top right of the member's page, you can put a support member back on the waiting list. Their annual fee or number of share capital remains unchanged.

### Inactive

An inactive member is one who does not have a subscription for the current or future fiscal year and does not have an annual fee set or have share capital. An inactive member can be put on the waiting list again or moved to support.

To move an inactive member to support, edit the member's profile and set an annual fee amount (even 0 for non-paying support members).

Using the "Put on waiting list" button at the top right of the member's page, you can put an inactive member on the waiting list. Their annual fee will then be reset to the organization's default value.

## <%= Member.human_attribute_name(:salary_basket) %> {#salary-basket}

The "<%= Member.human_attribute_name(:salary_basket) %>" flag on a member's profile indicates that this member receives their <%= Basket.model_name.human.downcase %> as part of their salary (e.g. farm employees). When enabled:

- All membership prices are set to zero (the membership still exists for delivery tracking, but nothing is billed).
- The member is excluded from billing reports and previsional invoicing.
- The default number of requested <%= activities_human_name.downcase %> is set to 0.
- The member is excluded from [bidding rounds](/handbook/bidding_round).

If the flag is toggled on an existing member, their current and future memberships are automatically recalculated.

## Food note & delivery note {#notes}

Two free-text fields are available on each member's profile:

- **Food note**: Allergies, preferences, or dietary information. This note can be displayed on [delivery sheet PDFs](/handbook/deliveries#delivery-sheets) if the corresponding [setting](/settings#delivery) is enabled.
- **Delivery note**: Practical delivery instructions (door code, floor, etc.). This note is always shown on home delivery sheets. Members can edit their own delivery note from their account.

Both fields appear in member exports (CSV/XLSX) and are cleared when a member is [anonymized](/handbook/right_to_be_forgotten).

## Different billing address {#billing-address}

If a member's invoices should be sent to a different address (e.g. a company or a relative), enable the "Different billing address" option in the member's profile under the "Billing" section. This reveals additional fields for a separate billing name, street, ZIP, and city. Members can also manage this from their own account.

## Contact sharing {#contact-sharing}

Members can opt in to share their contact details with other members at the same depot and delivery. See the dedicated [contact sharing handbook page](/handbook/contact_sharing) for details.

## Member account {#member-account}

Each member has access to a personal account on [their member account](<%= Current.org.members_url %>). Login is passwordless: the member enters their email address on [the login page](<%= Current.org.members_url %>/login) and receives a link valid for 15 minutes. Once logged in, the session lasts one year.

From their account, members can:

- **View deliveries**: See their next, future, and past <%= Basket.model_name.human(count: 2).downcase %>, including content details when available.
- **Order from the shop**: Place orders before the next delivery.
- **Sign up for <%= activities_human_name.downcase %>**: Browse and register for upcoming activities.
- **Manage absences**: Declare upcoming absences.
- **Manage billing**: View open invoices (with PDF) and their full payment history.
- **Edit their profile**: Update name, address, contact details, language, and delivery note.
- **Subscribe to a calendar**: Add their deliveries and <%= activities_human_name.downcase %> to any calendar app via an iCal feed.
- **Browse newsletters**: Read past newsletters they've received.
- **Delete their account**: Request account deletion (with email confirmation), in accordance with [the right to be forgotten](/handbook/right_to_be_forgotten).

If the organization has configured an [information page](/settings#member_information), it also appears in the member's navigation.

### Admin access to a member account {#admin-access}

From a member's admin page, the "Access account" button lets you open the member account as that member. This is useful for checking what a member sees or troubleshooting an issue. Admin-originated sessions expire after 6 hours (instead of the usual year).
